# Golden Toolbox — Business Checkup environment variables
# Copy this file to `.env` and fill in real values. `.env` is gitignored.
# In production, set these in Vercel → Project → Settings → Environment Variables.

# --- Google PageSpeed Insights (FREE, no billing) — priority #2 ---
PAGESPEED_API_KEY=

# --- Google Places / Maps Platform (billing enabled, lives in free credit) — priority #4 ---
GOOGLE_PLACES_API_KEY=
# Daily cap on Places "requests" (1 details + 1 text search = 2 per live report) as a cost safety net.
# PLACES_DAILY_CAP=300

# --- Directory Presence (priority #6): Google (via Places above) + Facebook,
# both real and free. Yelp's free Fusion tier was discontinued (now a 30-day
# trial into $229+/mo plans) — fails the zero-cost requirement, so it's left
# out. api/_lib/yelp.js exists but isn't wired in; Yelp's row stays mock,
# structured so a compliant source can be swapped in later.
# Facebook detection needs no key — it reuses the site HTML already fetched
# for the Techno Stack scan (see api/_lib/htmlscan.js).

# --- Upstash Redis (free tier) — cache + rate limits + spend log — priority #7 ---
# When BOTH are set, the store switches from deterministic mock mode to Upstash.
# UPSTASH_REDIS_REST_URL=
# UPSTASH_REDIS_REST_TOKEN=

# --- Admin manual-trigger secret — priority #8 ---
# Any long random string; used as the x-admin-secret header.
# ADMIN_SECRET=

# --- Lead notification (already live) ---
# Defaults to the existing Formspree endpoint if unset.
# FORMSPREE_ENDPOINT=https://formspree.io/f/mgojwopl
